Have you tried modifying the following line in your config.sys file:

DEVICE=X:\OS2\COMM.SYS to

DEVICE=X:\OS2\COMM.SYS (4,4e8,11)

where X is the partition OS/2 is installed (like C)

There should be no need to use the SIO drivers under Warp.

Do your OS/2 comm programs work or is it just the windows programs
that don't work?

>I own a soundblaster 16 MCD. This soundcard works great until I try the
>fastload option. Then, my sound goes away, and I get errors on any
>windows programs I start.  I tried disabling the sound device in the
>settings to no avail. Please help!!!!!

Not a bug.
With Fastload, the Windows Code is taking hold of the souncard (since
windows has system sounds) the first windows program you load, or
in this case the windows code itself using fastload, gets the use of the soundcard,
blocking other programs from using it.

The choice is to either disable fastload and get back your windows sound, or
keep fastload and disable windows sound. ( I don't use fastload with Warp
since the windows apps. load fast enough for me as is).


