Does your CD-ROM work at all or just that you couldn't read the TCP/IP
software off the CD-ROM?

If your CD-ROM is working, then I would use the Bonus Pak install routine:

go to an OS/2 screen (windowed or full) and change your directory to
the CD-ROM.  Then change directory to the US directory on the CDROM;
type INSTALL.  A nice menu will come-up (and music play in the background)
that lists the Bonus Pak software, allowing you to select what you want
to install (including the TCP/IP stuff).


